Comm360 Priority Areas [id=priority_areas]
----------------------

Lianne: Sure. The mission of Comm360 is to address community-based needs and issues through responsive programming in four priority areas.

Lianne: Education and Training includes programs designed to equip individuals with knowledge and skills for academic and career success, like after-school tutoring, GED prep, and workforce readiness.

Lianne: Health and Wellness focuses on initiatives for physical and mental well-being, providing accessible healthcare and wellness support. Examples include community health screenings, mental health counseling, and nutrition programs.

Lianne: Family and Youth Services provides support aimed at strengthening families and empowering youth through mentorship and essential resources, like parenting workshops, youth leadership, and conflict resolution training.

Lianne: Community Building and Advocacy involves efforts to foster civic engagement, policy awareness, and community development through inclusive initiatives. Examples include voter education, neighborhood revitalization, diversity workshops, advocating for changes in school curriculum and instruction, and equitable school funding.

Lianne: Now we can review how the causes we identified earlier map onto these priority areas of our nonprofit.

